@startuml Reciprocal Benchmarking Pool
title **Reciprocity: Contribute-to-Access Benchmarking Pool**\nOnly participants who share their own data can access others'

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #424242
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #9E9E9E
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #F9A825
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #E8F5E9
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #2E7D32
skinparam sequenceDividerBackgroundColor #F3E5F5

actor "Sarah Chen\n(White Buffalo)\n//contributing//" as Sarah #E8F5E9
actor "New Rancher\n(just onboarded)\n//observer//" as Newbie #FFF3E0
participant "Governance\nKeycloak" as KC #F3E5F5
participant "Caney Fork\nEDC Connector" as CF_EDC #E8F5E9
actor "Will Thompson\n(Caney Fork)\n//contributing//" as Will #E8F5E9

== Setup: Contribution status in Keycloak ==

note over KC
  The Dataspace Authority maintains
  a **contributionStatus** attribute
  for each participant:

  | Participant | Status |
  | Caney Fork | **contributing** |
  | White Buffalo | **contributing** |
  | New Rancher | **observer** |

  "Contributing" means the participant
  has published at least one dataset
  to the dataspace. Verified by the
  governance team.
end note

Will -> CF_EDC : Publishes grazing rotation data\nwith **contributing-members** access\n+ **reciprocal-benchmarking-terms** contract

== Sarah (contributing member) queries catalog ==

Sarah -> CF_EDC : DSP Catalog Query
note right of Sarah
  Token claims:
  glcdi_membership: **active**
  glcdi_roles: [glcdi_member, glcdi_producer]
  **glcdi_contribution_status: "contributing"**
end note

group Access Policy: contributing-members
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : membership == "active" ? **YES**
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : contributionStatus == "contributing" ? **YES**
  note right of CF_EDC
    Sarah has published her own data.
    => Grazing rotation **VISIBLE**
  end note
end

CF_EDC --> Sarah : Catalog includes grazing rotation

Sarah -> CF_EDC : Negotiate contract\npurpose = "RegionalBenchmarking"

group Contract Policy: reciprocal-benchmarking-terms
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : purpose in ["RegionalBenchmarking",\n"InternalAnalysis"] ? **YES**
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : dateTime <= 2026-09-30 ? **YES**
  note right of CF_EDC
    Duties accepted:
    - **Share back** benchmarking results
    - **Attribute** data source
    => **AGREED**
  end note
end

CF_EDC --> Sarah : Contract FINALIZED
Sarah -> CF_EDC : Transfer request
CF_EDC --> Sarah : Grazing rotation data

note over Sarah
  Sarah receives Will's data and
  runs her benchmarking analysis.

  **Reciprocity obligation:**
  She must share her benchmarking
  results (e.g., "your rest periods
  are 50% longer than mine, correlating
  with 12% higher SOC") back with Will.
end note

|||

== New Rancher (observer) queries catalog ==

Newbie -> CF_EDC : DSP Catalog Query
note right of Newbie
  Token claims:
  glcdi_membership: **active**
  glcdi_roles: [glcdi_member, glcdi_producer]
  **glcdi_contribution_status: "observer"**
end note

group Access Policy: contributing-members #FFEBEE
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : membership == "active" ? **YES**
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : contributionStatus == "contributing" ?\n"observer" != "contributing" => **NO**
  note right of CF_EDC #FFCDD2
    New Rancher has not published
    any data yet.
    => Grazing rotation **HIDDEN**
  end note
end

CF_EDC --> Newbie : Catalog does NOT include\ngrazing rotation

note over Newbie
  **What the new rancher sees:**
  Only assets with members-only access
  (no contribution requirement).

  **How to unlock the benchmarking pool:**
  1. Publish their own grazing/SOC data
     on their connector
  2. Notify the governance team
  3. Dataspace Authority verifies and
     updates contributionStatus
     from "observer" to "contributing"
  4. Next catalog query will show
     the benchmarking pool assets
end note

== New Rancher contributes and unlocks access ==

Newbie -> Newbie : Publishes own grazing data\non their connector
Newbie -> KC : Requests status update
KC -> KC : Dataspace Authority verifies\npublished assets
KC -> KC : Sets contributionStatus\n= "contributing"

Newbie -> CF_EDC : DSP Catalog Query (new token)
note right of Newbie
  Updated token:
  **glcdi_contribution_status: "contributing"**
end note

group Access Policy: contributing-members
  CF_EDC -> CF_EDC : contributionStatus == "contributing" ? **YES**
  note right of CF_EDC
    => Grazing rotation now **VISIBLE**
  end note
end

CF_EDC --> Newbie : Catalog now includes\ngrazing rotation

note over Newbie, Will
  **The reciprocity loop is complete:**
  - Will shared → Sarah accessed → Sarah shared back results
  - New Rancher contributed → gained access → will share back too
  - Every consumer is also a contributor
  - The benchmarking pool grows with each participant
end note

@enduml
